		<div id="post-4606" class="cf post-4606 post type-post status-publish format-standard category-uncategorized">

			<h1>
				<a href="http://werblog.com/2013/04/twitter-updates-2013-04-05-to-2013-04-11/" title="Twitter Updates: 2013-04-05 to 2013-04-11" rel="bookmark">Twitter Updates: 2013-04-05 to 2013-04-11</a>
				
			</h1>

			<div class="post-footer">
				12 Apr 2013 &nbsp;&nbsp;| <a href="http://werblog.com/category/uncategorized/">Uncategorized</a>
				
			</div>

			<div class="post-bodycopy cf">
				<ul class="ws_tweet_list">
<li class="ws_tweet">Stoked 2 have u as a student! MT <a href="http://twitter.com/ccarfi">@ccarfi</a>: Incredibly stoked to start diving into Gamification course via Coursera. <a href="https://t.co/mdXoKp7ePe" rel="nofollow">https://t.co/mdXoKp7ePe</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/320171811604152320">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Demand better. MOOCs can push us 2 improve teaching. MT <a href="http://twitter.com/NishithSharma">@NishithSharma</a> Never had any course been as interesting as this one. <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23gamification13">#gamification13</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/320172408428457986">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Who said it was a course? It&#039;s a game. ðŸ˜‰  MT <a href="http://twitter.com/wesselpeeters">@wesselpeeters</a>: Taking the <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23gamification13">#gamification13</a> course <a href="http://twitter.com/coursera">@coursera</a> doesn&#039;t even feel like a course. <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/320173411122958337">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Yes&#8230; but our kids know even more!  RT <a href="http://twitter.com/nikacanika">@nikacanika</a>: <a href="http://twitter.com/MarenziDesign">@MarenziDesign</a> <a href="http://twitter.com/kwerb">@kwerb</a> I&#039;ve being thinking we parents know a lot about gamification! <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/320175863473795072">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Getting ready for the Silfen  Forum on online learning at Penn,  featuring Tom Friedman,  Daphne Koller,  and others. <a href="http://t.co/KYkDTgPbD9" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/KYkDTgPbD9</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/320203868732547073">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Penn president Amy Guttman opens forum on online learning by quoting Plato.  Too bad <a href="http://twitter.com/sivavaid">@sivavaid</a> isn&#039;t here to heckle. <a href="http://t.co/Nyfm6lco1M" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/Nyfm6lco1M</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/320207452228444161">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Managing a MOOC while watching a panel discussion about MOOCs. <a href="http://t.co/F75q9id7kw" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/F75q9id7kw</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/320209894017994753">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Tom Friedman: &quot;My one rule in a flat world: Whatever can be done, will be done. Only question is whether it will be done by you or to you.&quot; <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/320210793809469441">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">FYI, <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23courseraconfatp">#courseraconfatp</a>enn is the hashtag for the Coursera partner conference going on now at Penn. Lots of great discussions around MOOCs. <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/320282024017543168">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Takeaway from copyright panel at <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23courseraconfatp">#courseraconfatp</a>enn: we aren&#039;t talking to each other enough, which leads to excessive access restrictions. <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/320293350806781952">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">David Brooks does not understand how teaching and learning work. &quot;Deliberate seminars&quot;? <a href="http://t.co/OUcndut7D1" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/OUcndut7D1</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/320527315668987906">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Biggest thing I&#039;m learning at <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23CourseraConfAtP">#CourseraConfAtP</a>enn is the vast amount of MOOC activity at scores of universities. Way more than recognized. <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/320534055819026432">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Any PhD students out there doing (or looking to do) research on <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23gamification">#gamification</a>? I&#039;ve been in touch with a couple but I&#039;m curious. <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/320563556498145281">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Big realization from <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23courseraconfatp">#courseraconfatp</a>enn: My Wharton colleagues and I are outliers in taking a DIY approach to MOOC development. <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/320568542154080256">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Staffing MOOCs with instructional designers, AV staff, developers, editors, etc. RT <a href="http://twitter.com/RobbyMeals">@RobbyMeals</a>: what are approaches other that diy? <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/320578764889276417">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Spam subject line of the day: &quot;Have you ever considered working on the internet?&quot; <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/320997813066555392">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Thanks! <a href="http://twitter.com/bingfish">@bingfish</a> is a fun guy to talk to. RT <a href="http://twitter.com/HostJoost">@HostJoost</a>: Great interview Bing Gordon and <a href="http://twitter.com/kwerb">@kwerb</a> on <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23gamification13">#gamification13</a> at <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23coursera">#coursera</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/321244258759766016">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">I tried to make them part of the learning. MT <a href="http://twitter.com/aoladi">@aoladi</a>: Thanks for the interesting first assignment to us Coursera <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23gamification13">#gamification13</a> students! <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/321589597538775040">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">About to do a video lecture on <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23gamification">#gamification</a> for <a href="http://twitter.com/digitaloctober">@digitaloctober</a> <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23knowledgestream">#knowledgestream</a> in Russia. View it here: <a href="http://t.co/A1jkUxAOv4" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/A1jkUxAOv4</a> <a href="http://twitter.com/digitaloctober/statuses/3.2164870584336E+17">in reply to digitaloctober</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/321650227146792961">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Mwaaahahahahaaa!!!  RT <a href="http://twitter.com/catswhiskerscat">@catswhiskerscat</a>: <a href="http://twitter.com/kwerb">@kwerb</a> I am now addicted to Plants vs Zombies and I *never* play computer games :0) <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/321731529845919744">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Certainly! Maybe some discussion here? MT <a href="http://twitter.com/DemetriouPan">@DemetriouPan</a>: Would it be ok for me to share key takeaways from your course on twitter please? <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/322103142336573440">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet"><a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%2310yf">#10yf</a> institute for the future future meeting starting in Sausalito <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/322380268201721856">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">It can be our little secret. RT <a href="http://twitter.com/crozo">@crozo</a>: Nobody believes I am doing homework while playing plants vs zombies. <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/322446101233934338">-&gt;</a></li>
</ul>

				
			</div>

			
			


